---
import PortalLayout from '../layouts/PortalLayout.astro';
---

<PortalLayout title="Playbook">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Spirit Media Playbook</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Architecture, workflows, and standards for every site we build</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Full Stack -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Full Stack</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div><strong>Astro + Tailwind CSS</strong> — pages and styling</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div><strong>GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Spirit-Media-US</a>)</strong> — code only, never media</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div><strong>Netlify</strong> — hosting, auto-deploys on push to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">main</code></div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — domain, SSL, CDN, security</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — all images, audio, video</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div><strong>Sanity (<a href="https://sanity.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">sanity.io</a>)</strong> — CMS for client content editing and media management with auto-optimization</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div><strong>GoHighLevel</strong> — all contact forms, tagged by site</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div><strong>Claude (<a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">claude.ai</a>)</strong> — conversational updates and builds</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div><strong>UptimeRobot</strong> — uptime monitoring <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 font-normal">(pending setup)</span></div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Launching a New Site -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Launching a New Site</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5">

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Phase 1 — Infrastructure</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
              <li>✓ Create public GitHub repo under Spirit-Media-US</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Add .gitignore blocking all media types</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Connect to Netlify (Spirit Media team, <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run build</code>, publish dir: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">dist</code>)</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Create R2 bucket, enable public URL</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Add domain to Cloudflare, activate proxy</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Phase 2 — Structure</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
              <li>✓ Initialize Astro + Tailwind locally</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Create all pages</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Build global nav and footer</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Rough in hero and page layouts</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Phase 3 — Design and Content</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
              <li>✓ Add all copy</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Upload media to R2, wire up URLs in code</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Add SEO meta per page (title + description)</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Refine design and UX</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Phase 4 — Launch</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
              <li>✓ Connect custom domain in Netlify</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Confirm SSL (www and apex) in Cloudflare</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Submit sitemap to Google Search Console</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Set up UptimeRobot monitoring</li>
              <li class="ml-4">— Enable analytics (Fathom or Plausible)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Media -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Media</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Media never goes in GitHub. All repos block this via .gitignore. For media-heavy sites (portfolios, artist sites), use Sanity — it handles uploads, auto-optimizes images, and serves them via its own CDN. For video, use YouTube — embeds on site and adds SEO value. For audio, use Cloudflare R2. R2 can also serve as a backup for video if YouTube isn't appropriate for a given client. Once a file is live, never rename or delete it or it will break on the site.</p>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800 mb-4">
          ⚠️ <strong>Never rename or delete a live media file</strong> — it will break every page that references it.
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">How to add media</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span> Client shares Google Drive folder with Kevin</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span> Kevin downloads and unzips</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span> Drag files into the site R2 bucket at <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">dash.cloudflare.com</a></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span> File is live immediately at the public URL</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span> Kevin or team updates site code to point to the new R2 URL</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Team Prompt -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Team Prompt</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-3">Paste at the top of every new Claude chat to give full project context.</p>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="bg-stone-100 border border-stone-200 rounded p-4 font-mono text-xs text-stone-700 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="team-prompt">You are helping Spirit Media Publishing build and maintain websites. Stack: Astro + Tailwind CSS. GitHub org: Spirit-Media-US (all repos public). Hosting: Netlify, Spirit Media team, build = npm run build, publish = dist. DNS/SSL/CDN: Cloudflare, proxy active. Media: Sanity (sanity.io) for images on media-heavy sites — auto-optimizes and serves via CDN. Cloudflare R2 for audio. Video goes on YouTube and is embedded on site. R2 is backup for video when YouTube isn't appropriate. Never put media in GitHub, all repos block this via .gitignore. Forms: GoHighLevel, all contacts tagged by site.

This site: [site name] | Repo: github.com/Spirit-Media-US/[repo-name] | Domain: [domain] | R2 bucket: [bucket-name or n/a]

Rules: Never push without local preview first (npm run dev). All work goes to the dev branch — never push directly to main. Only merge dev to main when Kevin says "push to main." Pricing off all public pages. All contacts to GHL. Media always to R2 or Sanity.

Today's task: [describe what you need]</div>
          <button id="copy-prompt-btn" class="mt-3 px-4 py-2 bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 hover:bg-white hover:border-red-700 text-red-700 text-xs font-semibold rounded transition-colors">Copy Prompt</button>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Development Infrastructure -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Development Infrastructure</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Server</h3>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-1">178.156.183.139</div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">CCX33 Hetzner — Ubuntu 22.04, all project repos at <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">/home/deploy/Sites/</code></p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Code Server (VS Code in browser)</h3>
            <a href="https://dev.spiritmediapublishing.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline text-sm font-mono">dev.spiritmediapublishing.com</a>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-1">Requires Tailscale VPN. Full IDE access to all repos.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Tailscale VPN</h3>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700">100.114.220.65</div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-1">Required for SSH and code-server access</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Deployment Workflow -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Deployment Workflow</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-4">All work happens on <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">dev</code>. Only merge to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">main</code> when ready to publish. Each push to main = one Netlify build credit.</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">1. Switch to dev</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git checkout dev</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">2. Preview locally</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">npm run dev</code>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">localhost:4321 — never push without previewing first</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">3. Commit and push to dev</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git add . && git commit --no-verify -m "message" && git push origin dev</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">4. Merge to main to publish</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git checkout main && git merge dev && git push origin main && git checkout dev</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Best Practices -->
      <section class="bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Best Practices</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 text-sm">
          <li>✓ Always preview before pushing: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run dev</code></li>
          <li>✓ Always build before merging to main: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run build</code></li>
          <li>✓ Never commit media files to Git</li>
          <li>✓ Never rename or delete a live media file</li>
          <li>✓ One push to main per session — batch all changes first</li>
          <li>✓ Pricing off all public pages</li>
          <li>✓ All form submissions route to GHL, tagged by site</li>
          <li>✓ Keep .env files in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">/home/deploy/bin/</code></li>
          <li>✓ Use meaningful commit messages</li>
          <li>✓ Kevin approves all merges to main</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Resources -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Resources</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li><a href="https://docs.astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Astro Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.sanity.io/docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Sanity Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Tailwind CSS Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://docs.netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Netlify Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Cloudflare Dashboard</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Spirit-Media-US GitHub</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</PortalLayout>

<script>
  document.getElementById('copy-prompt-btn')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    const text = document.getElementById('team-prompt')?.textContent || '';
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
      this.textContent = 'Copied!';
      setTimeout(() => { this.textContent = 'Copy Prompt'; }, 2000);
    });
  });
</script>
